          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>How does subtraction work in Roman numerals?</summary>
            <p>When a smaller value precedes a larger one, it is subtracted. IV = 4 (5−1), IX = 9 (10−1), XL = 40, XC = 90, CD = 400, CM = 900.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is 2024 in Roman numerals?</summary>
            <p>2024 in Roman numerals is MMXXIV — MM (2000) + XX (20) + IV (4).</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is the largest Roman numeral?</summary>
            <p>The classical system goes up to 3,999 (MMMCMXCIX). Larger numbers required bars over letters to multiply by 1,000.</p>
          </details>
